DataElement.preferredDefinition: Far apart in space, time, or relevance from a point of origin.:An individual who conducts scientific research. In a clinical setting this individual actually conducts and/or supervises the clinical investigation and study-related procedures.  The investigator monitors the safety of the trial subjects and investigational staff (under whose immediate direction an agent is administered or dispensed to a subject).  The investigator collects and analyses data and study documents, and provides reports in compliance with applicable requirements._A standardized representation of the geographical location of a person, business, building, or organization.  In the US this usually consists of a street name and number, a city, a state, and a zipcode._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
